CatDescriptText: Joan Williams, housewife, Third ward and Barbara Carson, housewife, North Side, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in the Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, May 21, 1960, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that racket squads eliminate vice and crime?" Mrs. William's answer reads: "Yes, I believe they do."  Mrs. Carson's answer reads: " I really don't know too much about rackets and racket squads, but form what I see I don't think they are doing much to cut down on rackets."
TitMainTitle: Two Frames: Portrait of Joan Williams wearing light colored floral pattered dress with dark belt, holding umbrella, seated in front of stone block wall with bushes, buildings in background; Portrait of Barbara Carson wearing dark paisley button down dress, holding eyeglasses, standing on sidewalk with automobiles and tall building in background
